headline: Does Grimes’ Return And AI Push Change The Bull Case For Morgan Stanley (MS)?
summary: Morgan Stanley recently rehired Michael Grimes as chairman of investment banking, underscoring the bank’s push into large technology IPOs, including a potential role in any future SpaceX listing following its merger with xAI and valuation of about US$1.25 trillion. Alongside this leadership move, Morgan Stanley is highlighting AI’s tangible business impact through new research and executive surveys, reinforcing a long-term focus on AI-enabled productivity gains, cost efficiencies and margin...

headline: Is It Too Late To Consider Buying Morgan Stanley (MS) After Its Strong Multi Year Rally
summary: If you are wondering whether Morgan Stanley is still good value after a strong multi year run, this article will walk through what the current share price might be implying about its worth. The stock recently closed at US$176.68, with a 1 year return of 32.3% and a 5 year return of 174.8%, even as the share price shows a 1.9% pullback over 7 days, a 5.3% decline over 30 days, and a 2.9% decline year to date.
